args: Form up, team! Now raise your hand\nif you're ready for THE GREATEST\ntreasure expedition of all time!
Thanks to you, Cleo. I'm so glad you\nall agreed to come along!
We'll try not to slow you down.
You handle the traps and navigation,\nand we will deal with the fiends.
Hoo boy, does this ever feel strange.\nI've never had treasure-hunting\ncompanions along for the ride before.
Mostly because I don't want to have to\ndivvy up the spoils at the end.
No alliances, no apprentices, and no one\nalong for the ride has always been my MO.
Don't worryâ€”ya ain't gonna regret\nhavin' us in yer corner.
I know I won't. Okay, off we go!
We've delved pretty deep into the ruins.
No way... But wait, it HAS to be!\nIt's this labyrinth's greatest treasureâ€”\nthe Crystal Doggo!
This is going to be the prize exhibit\nin my museum.
Then let's grab it and beat feet outta\nthis joint already!
Wait, Ranzal. That bridge between us and\nthe Doggo is narrow and flimsy. It might\ncollapse under our combined weight.
We should only send as many people\nacross as is absolutely necessary.
A horde of fiends is closing in behind us!
Well, that's a piece'a bad news.
All their stomping about might cause\nthe bridge to collapse!
No! Not when we're so close!
Go, Marty. Get the Crystal Doggo!\nThe bridge should hold if it's just you.
But I can't leave you here toâ€”
We'll hold the fiends off. Just go!
That's all well'n good, but now we gotta...\nDammit! That last one got past me!
No! The bridge collapsed!\nHow will Marty get back?
Don't worry, guys! I'll collect the Doggo\nand find another way out!
All right! We'll see you back\nat the Halidom!
Instead, why not feast your eyes on this\ntreasure and try NOT to have your jaw\nhit the floor!
Ta-dah! The Crystal Doggo, as promised.\nThings got a little hairy there at the end,\nbut I made it out all right.
And this is wonderful! Your museum will\nfinally have the treasure it deserves.\nYou've done Alberia a great service.
It is...but I can't keep the Doggo.
I may have been the one to find it, but I\ncouldn't have done it without your help.
We don't want the Doggo, Marty.\nIt's yours.
I knew you would say that!
But that still doesn't make it mine.\nIt's OURS, end of story.
All the same, I WOULD like to display it\nin my museum, so let's make a deal.
You let me look after the Doggo, and in\nreturn, I'll make myself useful here.
Are you sure? What happened to ï¼‚no\nalliances, no one along for the rideï¼‚?
Hey! I told you about that AFTER\nI agreed to team up, right?
But here I am, offering to share my hard-\nearned treasure. If that's not character\ngrowth, I don't know what is.
And more to the point, my old MO nearly\ngot me killed more than onceâ€”and\ndefinitely would have done so this time.
I'm not the ï¼‚greatestï¼‚ anything. Not yet.
If I'm going to prove myself as a curator,\nI need to learn to trust people more.
So how about it? Think there's a place\nfor me here at the ol' Halidom?
This is your home, if you want it to be.
I can't think of a place I'd rather be.
But in the meantime, point me at the\nnext treasâ€”Ah! Ow! My ribs!
I think right now what you need to hunt\nfor is some rest and relaxation.\nHold still while I heal you.
Ow, Cleo! What are you doing? You're\ngonna snap my bones in two. Ow ow oww!
That will teach him to worry us sick.
Heh. I think these silly moments together\nmight be my greatest treasure.
